BRITS,  October 30 – The trial against 14 people arrested for public violence in Majakaneng near Brits will resume at the Brits Magistrate’s Court in February next year. The accused appeared briefly in court on Tuesday for a pre-trial conference and their case was postponed to February 11. The trial is set to run for five days. In the pre-trial conference, the accused indicated they intend pleading not guilty to the charge of public violence. The State is set to call eight witnesses. All 14 people were released on bail and their bail was extended. (ANA)